             (Police-constable D 147.) On the 2nd of June, at half-past seven o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner turn into Cumberland-place, with a shawl in his hand - he ran down Bryanstone-street; I pursued, and asked him where he had got the shawl from - he said he had picked it up.</p>
